                        MICHAEL MONAGHAN
                  . (policeman, K 106). I produce a certificate—(Read: "Clerkenwell, April, 1856; 


                        George Green, Convicted of larceny; 
Confined four months")—this is the same man.





                        JOHN NEWELL
                  . (police sergeant, R 59). I produce a certificate—(Read: "Central Criminal Court, George Fraser, Convicted, Jan., 1852, of stealing 22lbs. horsehair, from a vessel, having been before convicted; 
Transported for seven years")—I was present—the prisoner is the person.
